channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Oscar Mayer Wienermobile Crashes Along Chicago Area Highway
item.description: The hot dog-shaped vehicle hit a car Monday morning and its driver lost control and overcorrected, causing it to roll onto its side on I-294.

item.title: Dad 'dismissed by doctors for 5 years as having piles' given devastating diagnosis
item.description: William Anderson, from Edinburgh, has told how he was in tremendous pain but claims that he was shrugged off by doctors including one who said he had piles before he was finally diagnosed

item.title: Sharks ‘high on cocaine’ after drugs are being flushed down the loo
item.description: It could be affecting their behaviour making them more aggressive.

item.title: Greg Rutherford teams up with innocent Drinks for 'crushing it summer games' to boost kids' fruit and veg intake
item.description: Greg Rutherford has joined forces with innocent Drinks to launch a new initiative aimed at getting kids to eat more fruits and vegetables - with just 23% currently hitting their five-a-day target

item.title: Psychic who envisioned Trump assassination attempt gives his US election prediction
item.description: 'I wasn't expecting this to happen until at least August this year.'

item.title: Beachgoer warning ahead of mini heatwave as BBQ fire destroys emergency phone line
item.description: People planning to visit the beach ahead of good weather expected next week are being warned not to throw away disposable barbecues before they have fully cooled

item.title: 14 children end up in hospital after trying ‘adult only’ crisps
item.description: The 'R18' crisps are made using an extract from the ultra-spicy ghost pepper.

item.title: Joe Biden 'hints at desire to remain in power' during Oval Office speech
item.description: Joe Biden explained why he pulled out of his second showdown with Donald Trump in an Oval Office address on Wednesday but a body language expert claims he secretly wishes to remain in power

item.title: Woman describes out of body aura she felt in near-death experience after crash
item.description: 'The experience has allowed me to see the beauty of life.'

item.title: Woman charged with murdering baby found in woods near Gulliver's World
item.description: Joanne Sharkey, 55, appeared in court charged with murder and endeavouring to conceal the birth of a child after the baby, who was later named as Callum, was discovered in woodland in Warrington in 1998
